Vice President Biden called Iraqi President Fuad Masum to discuss the government formation process in Baghdad and express the United States' support for his role as guarantor of the Iraqi Constitution. They discussed the nomination of Hayder al-Abadi as the next prime minister, and Biden commended Masum for this milestone. Biden reiterated President Obama's calls for the timely creation of a new, inclusive government that can address the concerns of all Iraqis. Biden also emphasized Obama's desire to coordinate with the new government and Iraqi Security Forces to counter the gains made by the Islamic State of Iraq and Levant. Masum thanked Biden for his support.